# Prisma & PostgreSQL Guardrails

## Query Best Practices
- Never execute raw SQL queries unless explicitly requested. Always use the Prisma Client instance (`prisma.round.create`, `prisma.playerProfile.findUnique`).
- Use proper relation inclusions (`include: { holes: true }`) to avoid N+1 query problems when rendering data on the performance dashboard.

## Transaction Safety
- When logging a complete post-round dataset, use Prisma transactions (`prisma.$transaction([...])`) to ensure that if saving a specific hole fails, the entire round is rolled back to prevent orphaned database records.